e's Debug implementation applies formatting rules separately to the start and to the end of the range.\r\n\r\nI tried this code:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nformat!(\"{:<10?} foo\", 0usize..10usize)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI expected to see this happen: Output of\r\n```rs\r\n\"0..10      foo\"`\r\n```\r\n\r\nInstead, this happened: Output of\r\n```rs\r\n\"0         ..10         foo\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Meta\r\nTested on latest nightly in the playground: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=932977922d8d8ae4f5def137c0f93ed2\r\n\r\n`rustc --version --verbose`:\r\n```\r\nrustc 1.55.0 (c8dfcfe04 2021-09-06)\r\nbinary: rustc\r\ncommit-hash: c8dfcfe046a7680554bf4eb612bad840e7631c4b\r\ncommit-date: 2021-09-06\r\nhost: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu\r\nrelease: 1.55.0\r\nLLVM version: 12.0.1\r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/90240/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/90240/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}